comments: Diallo (OKC) legally contests Schroder's (LAL) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Matthews (LAL) maintains a legal guarding position on Bazley (OKC) at the end of the drive and cleanly pokes the ball loose.
After Bazley (OKC) recovers the loose ball, James (LAL) makes clean ball contact to dislodge it from Bazley on his steal attempt.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) maintains a legal guarding position during the play at the basket by James (LAL) and makes clean ball contact on his dislodge attempt.
Schroder (LAL) maintains a legal guarding position on Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) during his drive.
Horford (OKC) is in the lane for longer than three seconds.
Harrell (LAL) jumps alongside of Dort's (OKC) path and absorbs the contact as Dort is naturally drifting away from the basket.
Diallo (OKC) moves laterally into Schroder's (LAL) path at the end of the drive and makes contact to his body that affects his SQBR.
Caldwell-Pope (LAL) establishes himself in a screening position in Dort's (OKC) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Bazley (OKC) maintains a straight-line path when Horton-Tucker (LAL) tries to cut through to the perimeter, and the contact is marginal as the two players come together.
Following the pick, Schroder (LAL) maintains a legal guarding position on Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) as he fumbles the hand-off before legally recovering and starting his dribble.
James (LAL) moves laterally into Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) path on the drive and the contact affects his SQBR.
The foul occurs when Horford (OKC) is in the lane for about three seconds.
Schroder (LAL) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC).
Horford (OKC) commits a take foul on Schroder (LAL).
During the rebound, Horton-Tucker (LAL) and Diallo (OKC) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.

Replay review of the foul called on Schroder (LAL) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful. Schroder cleanly blocks Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) driving shot attempt and any contact with Gilgeous-Alexander's hand on the ball is considered incidental.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) draws Caldwell-Pope (LAL) into the air towards him and the contact results in a foul on Caldwell-Pope (LAL) even if contact is initiated by Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC).
Harrell (LAL) establishes himself in a screening position in Dort's (OKC) path and absorbs the contact.
Dort (OKC) legally contests James' (LAL) jump shot attempt.
